.TH "__genwqe_wait_ddcb" 9 "__genwqe_wait_ddcb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__genwqe_wait_ddcb \- Waits until DDCB is completed
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __genwqe_wait_ddcb
.BI "(struct genwqe_dev *cd "  ","
.BI "struct ddcb_requ *req "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cd" 12
pointer to genwqe device descriptor
.IP "req" 12
pointer to requsted DDCB parameters
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The Service Layer will update the RETC in DDCB when processing is
pending or done.

When an error is returned the called needs to ensure that
\fBpurge_ddcb\fP is being called to get the \fIreq\fP removed from the
queue.
.SH "RETURN"
> 0 remaining jiffies, DDCB completed
-ETIMEDOUT when timeout
-ERESTARTSYS when ^C
-EINVAL when unknown error condition
